	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I definitely don't recoomand that. I cannot guarantee that your house will explode or anything, but current will continue to be drawn from the old battery and that is bad. It is actually easier to just replace it. As you mentionned, it's not a good idea to solver stuff direcly on a raw battery. I tried, and while I didn't do any damage to the cart, me or whathever, I just had to waste that battery and buy one with pins.
<br />Just disolver your old battery and place a new one with pins wich are similar to the circuit. Don't forget to recycle your old battery, and you're done.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


